Note:
==============================================================================
color_space - Color Space Conversion Registry
==============================================================================

This module implements the canonical "convert from any colour space to
any colour space" entrypoint used by the Runa colour subsystem. The
dispatch is staged through XYZ-D65 as a universal hub: every supported
space provides a forward (X -> XYZ-D65) and inverse (XYZ-D65 -> X)
transformation. End-to-end conversion is the composition.

Supported colour spaces (ColorSpace enum):

       0 SRGB           - non-linear sRGB
       1 LINEAR_RGB     - linear sRGB primaries (no transfer)
       2 DISPLAY_P3     - Display-P3 with sRGB-style transfer
       3 REC2020        - ITU-R BT.2020 wide-gamut HDR primaries
       4 ADOBE_RGB      - Adobe RGB (1998)
       5 PROPHOTO_RGB   - ProPhoto RGB (ROMM)
       6 XYZ_D50        - CIE 1931 XYZ at the D50 white point
       7 XYZ_D65        - CIE 1931 XYZ at the D65 white point (the hub)
       8 LAB            - CIELAB at D65
       9 LCH            - CIELCh at D65
      10 OKLAB          - Oklab (Ottosson 2020)
      11 OKLCH          - Oklch
      12 HSL            - HSL (CSS Color Module Level 4)
      13 HSV            - HSV (Smith 1978)

Chromatic adaptation between D50 and D65 white points uses the Bradford
matrix (J. Lam, "Calibrating the Bradford Chromatic Adaptation
Transform", 1985). The Bradford CAT matrix maps XYZ from the source
illuminant to the destination illuminant via three transforms:

           XYZ' = M_b XYZ
           XYZ' = D * XYZ'           (D is the diagonal ratio matrix)
           XYZ_out = M_b^{-1} XYZ'

with M_b the Bradford "cone response" matrix.

References:
  - IEC 61966-2-1 (sRGB)
  - SMPTE RP 431-2 / SMPTE ST 2086 (Display-P3)
  - ITU-R BT.2020 (Rec2020)
  - ANSI/CTA-861-G (P3-D65 primaries)
  - Adobe RGB (1998) specification
  - K. E. Spaulding et al, "Reference Output Medium Metric RGB Color
    Encoding (ROMM RGB)", PICS 2000 (ProPhoto)
  - J. Lam, "Calibrating the Bradford CAT", 1985
==============================================================================
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/arithmetic_core.runa" as Arith
