Note: ============================================================================
Note: INVERSE PRIMARY MATRICES: XYZ -> linear-RGB
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "xyz_to_linear_rgb_r" takes x as Float, y as Float, z as Float, space as Integer returns Float:
    @Reasoning
    Compute R from XYZ. The space argument selects which working RGB
    space; 0/1 = sRGB matrix, 2 = Display-P3 inverse, 3 = Rec.2020
    inverse, 4 = Adobe RGB inverse, 5 = ProPhoto inverse.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Per-space dispatch on the inverse matrix coefficients.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Three multiplies + two adds + one branch.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    If space is equal to 2:
        Return ((2.4934969 multiplied by x) minus (0.9313836 multiplied by y)) minus (0.4027108 multiplied by z)
    End If
    If space is equal to 3:
        Return ((1.7166512 multiplied by x) minus (0.3556708 multiplied by y)) minus (0.2533663 multiplied by z)
    End If
    If space is equal to 4:
        Return ((2.0413690 multiplied by x) minus (0.5649464 multiplied by y)) minus (0.3446944 multiplied by z)
    End If
    If space is equal to 5:
        Return ((1.3459433 multiplied by x) minus (0.2556075 multiplied by y)) minus (0.0511118 multiplied by z)
    End If
    Return ((3.2404542 multiplied by x) minus (1.5371385 multiplied by y)) minus (0.4985314 multiplied by z)
End Process

Process called "xyz_to_linear_rgb_g" takes x as Float, y as Float, z as Float, space as Integer returns Float:
    @Reasoning
    Compute G from XYZ.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Per-space dispatch.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Three multiplies + two adds + one branch.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    If space is equal to 2:
        Return (((0.0 minus 0.8294890) multiplied by x) plus (1.7626641 multiplied by y)) plus (0.0236247 multiplied by z)
    End If
    If space is equal to 3:
        Return (((0.0 minus 0.6666844) multiplied by x) plus (1.6164812 multiplied by y)) plus (0.0157685 multiplied by z)
    End If
    If space is equal to 4:
        Return (((0.0 minus 0.9692660) multiplied by x) plus (1.8760108 multiplied by y)) plus (0.0415560 multiplied by z)
    End If
    If space is equal to 5:
        Return (((0.0 minus 0.5445989) multiplied by x) plus (1.5081673 multiplied by y)) plus (0.0205351 multiplied by z)
    End If
    Return (((0.0 minus 0.9692660) multiplied by x) plus (1.8760108 multiplied by y)) plus (0.0415560 multiplied by z)
End Process

Process called "xyz_to_linear_rgb_b" takes x as Float, y as Float, z as Float, space as Integer returns Float:
    @Reasoning
    Compute B from XYZ.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Per-space dispatch.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Three multiplies + two adds + one branch.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope
    If space is equal to 2:
        Return (((0.0358458 multiplied by x) minus (0.0761724 multiplied by y)) plus (0.9568845 multiplied by z))
    End If
    If space is equal to 3:
        Return (((0.0176399 multiplied by x) minus (0.0427706 multiplied by y)) plus (0.9421031 multiplied by z))
    End If
    If space is equal to 4:
        Return (((0.0134474 multiplied by x) minus (0.1183897 multiplied by y)) plus (1.0154096 multiplied by z))
    End If
    If space is equal to 5:
        Return ((0.0 multiplied by x) plus (0.0 multiplied by y)) plus (1.2118128 multiplied by z)
    End If
    Return (((0.0556434 multiplied by x) minus (0.2040259 multiplied by y)) plus (1.0572252 multiplied by z))
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BRADFORD CHROMATIC ADAPTATION (D50 <-> D65)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bradford_adapt_d50_to_d65" takes x as Float, y as Float, z as Float, out_xyz as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bradford chromatic-adaptation transform from D50 to D65. The full
    transform M_b^{-1} * D * M_b applied to the input XYZ. Writes the
    output into out_xyz at offsets 0, 8, 16.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Single precomputed combined 3x3 matrix derived from the Bradford
    CAT coefficients (Lam 1985).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Nine multiplies + six adds.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller owns out_xyz (24 bytes).
    @End Security_Scope
    Let xo be (((0.9555766 multiplied by x) plus ((0.0 minus 0.0230393) multiplied by y)) plus (0.0631636 multiplied by z))
    Let yo be ((((0.0 minus 0.0282895) multiplied by x) plus (1.0099416 multiplied by y)) plus (0.0210077 multiplied by z))
    Let zo be (((0.0122982 multiplied by x) minus (0.0204830 multiplied by y)) plus (1.3299098 multiplied by z))
    Let _wx be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 0, xo)
    Let _wy be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 8, yo)
    Let _wz be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 16, zo)
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "bradford_adapt_d65_to_d50" takes x as Float, y as Float, z as Float, out_xyz as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Inverse of bradford_adapt_d50_to_d65.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Inverse coefficients precomputed from Lam 1985.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Nine multiplies + six adds.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller owns out_xyz (24 bytes).
    @End Security_Scope
    Let xo be (((1.0478112 multiplied by x) plus (0.0228866 multiplied by y)) minus (0.0501270 multiplied by z))
    Let yo be (((0.0295424 multiplied by x) plus (0.9904844 multiplied by y)) minus (0.0170491 multiplied by z))
    Let zo be ((((0.0 minus 0.0092345) multiplied by x) plus (0.0150436 multiplied by y)) plus (0.7521316 multiplied by z))
    Let _wx be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 0, xo)
    Let _wy be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 8, yo)
    Let _wz be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 16, zo)
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "chromatic_adaptation_bradford" takes x as Float, y as Float, z as Float, src_white_x as Float, src_white_y as Float, src_white_z as Float, dst_white_x as Float, dst_white_y as Float, dst_white_z as Float, out_xyz as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    General Bradford chromatic adaptation between two arbitrary white
    points. Builds the cone-response ratios from the source and dest
    white points, then applies M_b^{-1} (D * (M_b XYZ_in)).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    The Bradford forward cone matrix M_b is:
       |  0.8951    0.2664   -0.1614 |
       | -0.7502    1.7135    0.0367 |
       |  0.0389   -0.0685    1.0296 |
    Inverse M_b^{-1}:
       |  0.9869929 -0.1470543  0.1599627 |
       |  0.4323053  0.5183603  0.0492912 |
       | -0.0085287  0.0400428  0.9684867 |
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Three matrix multiplies + three divides.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller owns out_xyz (24 bytes).
    @End Security_Scope
    Let rho_src be (((0.8951 multiplied by src_white_x) plus (0.2664 multiplied by src_white_y)) plus ((0.0 minus 0.1614) multiplied by src_white_z))
    Let gamma_src be ((((0.0 minus 0.7502) multiplied by src_white_x) plus (1.7135 multiplied by src_white_y)) plus (0.0367 multiplied by src_white_z))
    Let beta_src be (((0.0389 multiplied by src_white_x) plus ((0.0 minus 0.0685) multiplied by src_white_y)) plus (1.0296 multiplied by src_white_z))
    Let rho_dst be (((0.8951 multiplied by dst_white_x) plus (0.2664 multiplied by dst_white_y)) plus ((0.0 minus 0.1614) multiplied by dst_white_z))
    Let gamma_dst be ((((0.0 minus 0.7502) multiplied by dst_white_x) plus (1.7135 multiplied by dst_white_y)) plus (0.0367 multiplied by dst_white_z))
    Let beta_dst be (((0.0389 multiplied by dst_white_x) plus ((0.0 minus 0.0685) multiplied by dst_white_y)) plus (1.0296 multiplied by dst_white_z))
    Let rho_in be (((0.8951 multiplied by x) plus (0.2664 multiplied by y)) plus ((0.0 minus 0.1614) multiplied by z))
    Let gamma_in be ((((0.0 minus 0.7502) multiplied by x) plus (1.7135 multiplied by y)) plus (0.0367 multiplied by z))
    Let beta_in be (((0.0389 multiplied by x) plus ((0.0 minus 0.0685) multiplied by y)) plus (1.0296 multiplied by z))
    Let rho_out be 0.0
    Let gamma_out be 0.0
    Let beta_out be 0.0
    If rho_src is not equal to 0.0:
        Set rho_out to rho_in multiplied by (rho_dst divided by rho_src)
    End If
    If gamma_src is not equal to 0.0:
        Set gamma_out to gamma_in multiplied by (gamma_dst divided by gamma_src)
    End If
    If beta_src is not equal to 0.0:
        Set beta_out to beta_in multiplied by (beta_dst divided by beta_src)
    End If
    Let xo be (((0.9869929 multiplied by rho_out) plus ((0.0 minus 0.1470543) multiplied by gamma_out)) plus (0.1599627 multiplied by beta_out))
    Let yo be (((0.4323053 multiplied by rho_out) plus (0.5183603 multiplied by gamma_out)) plus (0.0492912 multiplied by beta_out))
    Let zo be ((((0.0 minus 0.0085287) multiplied by rho_out) plus (0.0400428 multiplied by gamma_out)) plus (0.9684867 multiplied by beta_out))
    Let _wx be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 0, xo)
    Let _wy be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 8, yo)
    Let _wz be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 16, zo)
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TO-XYZ-D65: any RGB-family space -> XYZ-D65
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "rgb_space_to_xyz_d65" takes c1 as Float, c2 as Float, c3 as Float, space as Integer, out_xyz as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Apply the transfer (if any) for the source space then the forward
    matrix. Writes XYZ-D65 at out_xyz offsets 0/8/16.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Dispatches on space for transfer choice and primary matrix.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Three transfer evaluations + nine matrix FLOPs.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller owns out_xyz.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let r_lin be c1
    Let g_lin be c2
    Let b_lin be c3
    If space is equal to 0:
        Set r_lin to srgb_to_linear_cs(c1)
        Set g_lin to srgb_to_linear_cs(c2)
        Set b_lin to srgb_to_linear_cs(c3)
    End If
    If space is equal to 2:
        Set r_lin to srgb_to_linear_cs(c1)
        Set g_lin to srgb_to_linear_cs(c2)
        Set b_lin to srgb_to_linear_cs(c3)
    End If
    If space is equal to 3:
        Set r_lin to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(c1), 2.4)
        Set g_lin to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(c2), 2.4)
        Set b_lin to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(c3), 2.4)
    End If
    If space is equal to 4:
        Set r_lin to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(c1), 2.19921875)
        Set g_lin to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(c2), 2.19921875)
        Set b_lin to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(c3), 2.19921875)
    End If
    If space is equal to 5:
        Set r_lin to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(c1), 1.8)
        Set g_lin to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(c2), 1.8)
        Set b_lin to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(c3), 1.8)
    End If
    Let x_out be 0.0
    Let y_out be 0.0
    Let z_out be 0.0
    If space is equal to 2:
        Set x_out to linear_p3_to_xyz_x(r_lin, g_lin, b_lin)
        Set y_out to linear_p3_to_xyz_y(r_lin, g_lin, b_lin)
        Set z_out to linear_p3_to_xyz_z(r_lin, g_lin, b_lin)
    Otherwise:
        If space is equal to 3:
            Set x_out to linear_rec2020_to_xyz_x(r_lin, g_lin, b_lin)
            Set y_out to linear_rec2020_to_xyz_y(r_lin, g_lin, b_lin)
            Set z_out to linear_rec2020_to_xyz_z(r_lin, g_lin, b_lin)
        Otherwise:
            If space is equal to 4:
                Set x_out to ((0.5767309 multiplied by r_lin) plus (0.1855540 multiplied by g_lin)) plus (0.1881852 multiplied by b_lin)
                Set y_out to ((0.2973769 multiplied by r_lin) plus (0.6273491 multiplied by g_lin)) plus (0.0752741 multiplied by b_lin)
                Set z_out to ((0.0270343 multiplied by r_lin) plus (0.0706872 multiplied by g_lin)) plus (0.9911085 multiplied by b_lin)
            Otherwise:
                If space is equal to 5:
                    Set x_out to ((0.7976749 multiplied by r_lin) plus (0.1351917 multiplied by g_lin)) plus (0.0313534 multiplied by b_lin)
                    Set y_out to ((0.2880402 multiplied by r_lin) plus (0.7118741 multiplied by g_lin)) plus (0.0000857 multiplied by b_lin)
                    Set z_out to ((0.0 multiplied by r_lin) plus (0.0 multiplied by g_lin)) plus (0.8252100 multiplied by b_lin)
                Otherwise:
                    Set x_out to linear_srgb_to_xyz_x(r_lin, g_lin, b_lin)
                    Set y_out to linear_srgb_to_xyz_y(r_lin, g_lin, b_lin)
                    Set z_out to linear_srgb_to_xyz_z(r_lin, g_lin, b_lin)
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Let _wx be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 0, x_out)
    Let _wy be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 8, y_out)
    Let _wz be store_float_at_cs(out_xyz, 16, z_out)
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: FROM-XYZ-D65: XYZ-D65 -> any RGB-family space
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "xyz_d65_to_rgb_space" takes x as Float, y as Float, z as Float, space as Integer, out_rgb as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Apply the inverse primary matrix then the forward transfer function.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Per-space dispatch.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Nine matrix FLOPs + three transfer evaluations.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller owns out_rgb (24 bytes).
    @End Security_Scope
    Let r_lin be xyz_to_linear_rgb_r(x, y, z, space)
    Let g_lin be xyz_to_linear_rgb_g(x, y, z, space)
    Let b_lin be xyz_to_linear_rgb_b(x, y, z, space)
    Let r_out be r_lin
    Let g_out be g_lin
    Let b_out be b_lin
    If space is equal to 0:
        Set r_out to linear_to_srgb_cs(r_lin)
        Set g_out to linear_to_srgb_cs(g_lin)
        Set b_out to linear_to_srgb_cs(b_lin)
    End If
    If space is equal to 2:
        Set r_out to linear_to_srgb_cs(r_lin)
        Set g_out to linear_to_srgb_cs(g_lin)
        Set b_out to linear_to_srgb_cs(b_lin)
    End If
    If space is equal to 3:
        Let inv_24 be 1.0 divided by 2.4
        Set r_out to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(r_lin), inv_24)
        Set g_out to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(g_lin), inv_24)
        Set b_out to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(b_lin), inv_24)
    End If
    If space is equal to 4:
        Let inv_22 be 1.0 divided by 2.19921875
        Set r_out to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(r_lin), inv_22)
        Set g_out to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(g_lin), inv_22)
        Set b_out to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(b_lin), inv_22)
    End If
    If space is equal to 5:
        Let inv_18 be 1.0 divided by 1.8
        Set r_out to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(r_lin), inv_18)
        Set g_out to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(g_lin), inv_18)
        Set b_out to pow_real_cs(absf_cs(b_lin), inv_18)
    End If
    Let _wr be store_float_at_cs(out_rgb, 0, r_out)
    Let _wg be store_float_at_cs(out_rgb, 8, g_out)
    Let _wb be store_float_at_cs(out_rgb, 16, b_out)
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HIGH-LEVEL DISPATCH: color_space_convert
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "color_space_convert" takes c1 as Float, c2 as Float, c3 as Float, from_space as Integer, to_space as Integer, out_channels as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Convert a 3-channel colour value from one colour space to another by
    staging through XYZ-D65 as the universal hub. Covers every supported
    space (ids 0..13): sRGB, linear sRGB, Display-P3, Rec.2020,
    Adobe RGB, ProPhoto RGB, XYZ-D50, XYZ-D65, Lab, LCh, Oklab, Oklch,
    HSL, HSV. RGB-family inputs are linearised by the source-space
    transfer function then projected into XYZ-D65 via the primary
    matrices; cylindrical and perceptual spaces are routed through
    their dedicated modules (lab.runa, oklab.runa, hsl.runa).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Stage one: project the input triple to XYZ-D65 in xyz_buf. The path
    depends on from_space:
      0..5 -> rgb_space_to_xyz_d65 (RGB-family transfer + primary matrix)
      6    -> bradford_adapt_d50_to_d65 (white-point only)
      7    -> direct copy
      8    -> Lab.lab_to_xyz on the (L, a, b) input triple
      9    -> Lab.lch_to_lab then Lab.lab_to_xyz
     10    -> Oklab.oklab_create then Oklab.oklab_to_rgb to linear sRGB,
              then linear_srgb_to_xyz_*
     11    -> Oklab.oklch_create then Oklab.oklch_to_oklab and the same
              oklab-to-XYZ rail used by space 10
     12    -> Hsl.hsl_create then Hsl.hsl_to_rgb to non-linear sRGB,
              then srgb_to_linear_cs and linear_srgb_to_xyz_*
     13    -> Hsl.hsv_create then Hsl.hsv_to_rgb on the same rail
    Stage two: project xyz_buf to the destination space. The path
    depends on to_space:
      0..5 -> xyz_d65_to_rgb_space (inverse primary matrix + transfer)
      6    -> bradford_adapt_d65_to_d50
      7    -> direct copy
      8    -> Lab.xyz_create + Lab.xyz_to_lab; write (L, a, b)
      9    -> Lab.xyz_to_lab + Lab.lab_to_lch; write (L, C, h)
     10    -> xyz_d65_to_rgb_space for sRGB linear leg + Oklab.linear_rgb_to_oklab
     11    -> previous + Oklab.oklab_to_oklch; write (L, C, h)
     12    -> xyz_d65_to_rgb_space for non-linear sRGB + Hsl.hsl_from_rgb;
              write (h, s, l)
     13    -> previous + Hsl.hsv_from_rgb; write (h, s, v)
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two transfer-and-matrix legs in the RGB-family fast path. Lab/Oklab
    legs add three cbrt evaluations. HSL/HSV legs add the sextant
    dispatch (cheap). All scratch buffers are 24 bytes on the owned heap.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller owns out_channels (at least 24 bytes).
    @End Security_Scope
    Let xyz_buf be Layout.allocate(24)
    If xyz_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Note: Stage 1 - project input into XYZ-D65 in xyz_buf
    If from_space is equal to 6:
        Let _b be bradford_adapt_d50_to_d65(c1, c2, c3, xyz_buf)
    Otherwise:
        If from_space is equal to 7:
            Let _wx be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 0, c1)
            Let _wy be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 8, c2)
            Let _wz be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 16, c3)
        Otherwise:
            If from_space is equal to 8:
                Note: Lab(L, a, b) input
                Let lab_in be Lab.lab_create(c1, c2, c3)
                Let xyz_in be Lab.lab_to_xyz(lab_in)
                Let _wx be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 0, Lab.xyz_x(xyz_in))
                Let _wy be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 8, Lab.xyz_y(xyz_in))
                Let _wz be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 16, Lab.xyz_z(xyz_in))
            Otherwise:
                If from_space is equal to 9:
                    Note: LCh(L, C, h_deg) input
                    Let lch_in be Lab.lch_create(c1, c2, c3)
                    Let lab_from_lch be Lab.lch_to_lab(lch_in)
                    Let xyz_in9 be Lab.lab_to_xyz(lab_from_lch)
                    Let _wx9 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 0, Lab.xyz_x(xyz_in9))
                    Let _wy9 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 8, Lab.xyz_y(xyz_in9))
                    Let _wz9 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 16, Lab.xyz_z(xyz_in9))
                Otherwise:
                    If from_space is equal to 10:
                        Note: Oklab(L, a, b) input - via linear-RGB
                        Let oklab_in be Oklab.oklab_create(c1, c2, c3)
                        Let rgb_lin_buf be Layout.allocate(32)
                        If rgb_lin_buf is equal to 0:
                            Let _df be Layout.deallocate(xyz_buf)
                            Return 1
                        End If
                        Let _ol be Oklab.oklab_to_linear_rgb(oklab_in, rgb_lin_buf)
                        Let r_lin10 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_lin_buf, 0))
                        Let g_lin10 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_lin_buf, 8))
                        Let b_lin10 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_lin_buf, 16))
                        Let _drl be Layout.deallocate(rgb_lin_buf)
                        Let x10 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_x(r_lin10, g_lin10, b_lin10)
                        Let y10 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_y(r_lin10, g_lin10, b_lin10)
                        Let z10 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_z(r_lin10, g_lin10, b_lin10)
                        Let _wx10 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 0, x10)
                        Let _wy10 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 8, y10)
                        Let _wz10 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 16, z10)
                    Otherwise:
                        If from_space is equal to 11:
                            Note: Oklch(L, C, h_deg) input -> oklab -> linear-RGB -> XYZ
                            Let oklch_in be Oklab.oklch_create(c1, c2, c3)
                            Let oklab_from_oklch be Oklab.oklch_to_oklab(oklch_in)
                            Let rgb_lin_buf11 be Layout.allocate(32)
                            If rgb_lin_buf11 is equal to 0:
                                Let _df11 be Layout.deallocate(xyz_buf)
                                Return 1
                            End If
                            Let _ol11 be Oklab.oklab_to_linear_rgb(oklab_from_oklch, rgb_lin_buf11)
                            Let r_lin11 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_lin_buf11, 0))
                            Let g_lin11 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_lin_buf11, 8))
                            Let b_lin11 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_lin_buf11, 16))
                            Let _drl11 be Layout.deallocate(rgb_lin_buf11)
                            Let x11 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_x(r_lin11, g_lin11, b_lin11)
                            Let y11 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_y(r_lin11, g_lin11, b_lin11)
                            Let z11 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_z(r_lin11, g_lin11, b_lin11)
                            Let _wx11 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 0, x11)
                            Let _wy11 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 8, y11)
                            Let _wz11 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 16, z11)
                        Otherwise:
                            If from_space is equal to 12:
                                Note: HSL(h_deg, s, l) input -> non-linear sRGB -> linear -> XYZ
                                Let hsl_in be Hsl.hsl_create(c1, c2, c3, 1.0)
                                Let rgb_srgb_buf be Layout.allocate(32)
                                If rgb_srgb_buf is equal to 0:
                                    Let _df12 be Layout.deallocate(xyz_buf)
                                    Return 1
                                End If
                                Let _h12 be Hsl.hsl_to_rgb(hsl_in, rgb_srgb_buf)
                                Let r_s12 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_srgb_buf, 0))
                                Let g_s12 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_srgb_buf, 8))
                                Let b_s12 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_srgb_buf, 16))
                                Let _ds12 be Layout.deallocate(rgb_srgb_buf)
                                Let r_lin12 be srgb_to_linear_cs(r_s12)
                                Let g_lin12 be srgb_to_linear_cs(g_s12)
                                Let b_lin12 be srgb_to_linear_cs(b_s12)
                                Let x12 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_x(r_lin12, g_lin12, b_lin12)
                                Let y12 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_y(r_lin12, g_lin12, b_lin12)
                                Let z12 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_z(r_lin12, g_lin12, b_lin12)
                                Let _wx12 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 0, x12)
                                Let _wy12 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 8, y12)
                                Let _wz12 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 16, z12)
                            Otherwise:
                                If from_space is equal to 13:
                                    Note: HSV(h_deg, s, v) input -> non-linear sRGB -> linear -> XYZ
                                    Let hsv_in be Hsl.hsv_create(c1, c2, c3, 1.0)
                                    Let rgb_srgb_buf13 be Layout.allocate(32)
                                    If rgb_srgb_buf13 is equal to 0:
                                        Let _df13 be Layout.deallocate(xyz_buf)
                                        Return 1
                                    End If
                                    Let _h13 be Hsl.hsv_to_rgb(hsv_in, rgb_srgb_buf13)
                                    Let r_s13 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_srgb_buf13, 0))
                                    Let g_s13 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_srgb_buf13, 8))
                                    Let b_s13 be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(rgb_srgb_buf13, 16))
                                    Let _ds13 be Layout.deallocate(rgb_srgb_buf13)
                                    Let r_lin13 be srgb_to_linear_cs(r_s13)
                                    Let g_lin13 be srgb_to_linear_cs(g_s13)
                                    Let b_lin13 be srgb_to_linear_cs(b_s13)
                                    Let x13 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_x(r_lin13, g_lin13, b_lin13)
                                    Let y13 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_y(r_lin13, g_lin13, b_lin13)
                                    Let z13 be linear_srgb_to_xyz_z(r_lin13, g_lin13, b_lin13)
                                    Let _wx13 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 0, x13)
                                    Let _wy13 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 8, y13)
                                    Let _wz13 be store_float_at_cs(xyz_buf, 16, z13)
                                Otherwise:
                                    Let _r be rgb_space_to_xyz_d65(c1, c2, c3, from_space, xyz_buf)
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Let xv be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(xyz_buf, 0))
    Let yv be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(xyz_buf, 8))
    Let zv be bits_to_float_cs(Memory.memory_get_int64(xyz_buf, 16))
    Let _dxyz be Layout.deallocate(xyz_buf)
    Note: Stage 2 - project XYZ-D65 into destination space
    If to_space is equal to 6:
        Let _ba be bradford_adapt_d65_to_d50(xv, yv, zv, out_channels)
        Return 0
    End If
    If to_space is equal to 7:
        Let _wx be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 0, xv)
        Let _wy be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 8, yv)
        Let _wz be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 16, zv)
        Return 0
    End If
    If to_space is equal to 8:
        Let xyz_out8 be Lab.xyz_create(xv, yv, zv)
        Let lab_out8 be Lab.xyz_to_lab(xyz_out8)
        Let _wl8 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 0, Lab.lab_l(lab_out8))
        Let _wa8 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 8, Lab.lab_a(lab_out8))
        Let _wb8 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 16, Lab.lab_b(lab_out8))
        Return 0
    End If
    If to_space is equal to 9:
        Let xyz_out9 be Lab.xyz_create(xv, yv, zv)
        Let lab_inter9 be Lab.xyz_to_lab(xyz_out9)
        Let lch_out9 be Lab.lab_to_lch(lab_inter9)
        Let _wl9 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 0, Lab.lch_l(lch_out9))
        Let _wc9 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 8, Lab.lch_c(lch_out9))
        Let _wh9 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 16, Lab.lch_h(lch_out9))
        Return 0
    End If
    If to_space is equal to 10:
        Note: Convert XYZ to linear sRGB then linear sRGB to Oklab
        Let r_lin_out10 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_r(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let g_lin_out10 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_g(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let b_lin_out10 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_b(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let oklab_out10 be Oklab.linear_rgb_to_oklab(r_lin_out10, g_lin_out10, b_lin_out10)
        Let _wl10 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 0, Oklab.oklab_l(oklab_out10))
        Let _wa10 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 8, Oklab.oklab_a(oklab_out10))
        Let _wb10 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 16, Oklab.oklab_b(oklab_out10))
        Return 0
    End If
    If to_space is equal to 11:
        Let r_lin_out11 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_r(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let g_lin_out11 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_g(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let b_lin_out11 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_b(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let oklab_inter11 be Oklab.linear_rgb_to_oklab(r_lin_out11, g_lin_out11, b_lin_out11)
        Let oklch_out11 be Oklab.oklab_to_oklch(oklab_inter11)
        Let _wl11 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 0, Oklab.oklch_l(oklch_out11))
        Let _wc11 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 8, Oklab.oklch_c(oklch_out11))
        Let _wh11 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 16, Oklab.oklch_h(oklch_out11))
        Return 0
    End If
    If to_space is equal to 12:
        Note: XYZ -> linear sRGB -> non-linear sRGB -> HSL
        Let r_lin_out12 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_r(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let g_lin_out12 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_g(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let b_lin_out12 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_b(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let r_srgb12 be linear_to_srgb_cs(r_lin_out12)
        Let g_srgb12 be linear_to_srgb_cs(g_lin_out12)
        Let b_srgb12 be linear_to_srgb_cs(b_lin_out12)
        Let hsl_out12 be Hsl.hsl_from_rgb(r_srgb12, g_srgb12, b_srgb12, 1.0)
        Let _wh12 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 0, Hsl.hsl_h(hsl_out12))
        Let _ws12 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 8, Hsl.hsl_s(hsl_out12))
        Let _wl12 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 16, Hsl.hsl_l(hsl_out12))
        Return 0
    End If
    If to_space is equal to 13:
        Let r_lin_out13 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_r(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let g_lin_out13 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_g(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let b_lin_out13 be xyz_to_linear_rgb_b(xv, yv, zv, 1)
        Let r_srgb13 be linear_to_srgb_cs(r_lin_out13)
        Let g_srgb13 be linear_to_srgb_cs(g_lin_out13)
        Let b_srgb13 be linear_to_srgb_cs(b_lin_out13)
        Let hsv_out13 be Hsl.hsv_from_rgb(r_srgb13, g_srgb13, b_srgb13, 1.0)
        Let _wh13 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 0, Hsl.hsv_h(hsv_out13))
        Let _ws13 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 8, Hsl.hsv_s(hsv_out13))
        Let _wv13 be store_float_at_cs(out_channels, 16, Hsl.hsv_v(hsv_out13))
        Return 0
    End If
    Let _r be xyz_d65_to_rgb_space(xv, yv, zv, to_space, out_channels)
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BIT-CAST HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "float_to_bits_cs" takes x as Float returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bit-cast Float64 to its 64-bit integer pattern.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Inline assembly reads the float-occupying stack slot as integer.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single mov.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-16], rax
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bits_to_float_cs" takes b as Integer returns Float:
    @Reasoning
    Bit-cast a 64-bit pattern back to a Float64.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Inline assembly: store the integer into the Float-occupying stack
    slot and reload as Float.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single mov.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let result be 0.0
    Inline Assembly:
        mov rax, qword ptr [rbp-8]
        mov qword ptr [rbp-16], rax
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "store_float_at_cs" takes ptr as Integer, offset as Integer, value as Float returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bit-cast a Float64 and store at ptr + offset.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    float_to_bits_cs + memory_set_int64.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two movs + one store.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller owns ptr.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let bits be float_to_bits_cs(value)
    Let _w be Memory.memory_set_int64(ptr, offset, bits)
    Return 0
End Process
